snippet.textDisplay: So Liverpool are not quite but nearly the all-conquering team of the season and possibly more. This goes to illustrate in stark relief what happens when a team achieves its objective. The hunger for more is not quite there, See Manchester City. The assumption that the team will play as they have been for many seasons. See Manchester City. The same will happen to Liverpool as it has happened to many teams before, after they have had great success. There is no way that we can predict next season or the season after on the basis of what a team is doing this season. See Manchester City. Next seasons success is anybody's guess. At the moment, Liverpool seem to have the best chance, but a number of trailing clubs might raise their game, get that crucial new player or have the  rub of the green. This is what makes football so special and so unpredictable.
